did.unittitle: Gerard Salton papers.
did.physdesc: Correspondence, subject files, videocassettes, notebooks, manuscripts
did.repository: Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library
did.abstract: Subject files, correspondence, class notebooks, videocassettes, reprints, and other papers and records deriving from Salton's work in text processing, information retrieval, and computer science.

bioghist.head: BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE
bioghist.p: Professor of Computer Science, Cornell University. Salton has worked in the areas of natural language text processing, automatic text processing, and informational retrieval; editor-in-chief, Association for Computing Machinery Communications; Guggenheim Fellow, 1963.

scopecontent.head: COLLECTION DESCRIPTION
scopecontent.p: Subject files, correspondence, class notebooks, videocassettes, reprints, and other papers and records deriving from Salton's work in text processing, information retrieval, and computer science.
